quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  29,53,"They ask you to hasten the punishment. Had there not been an appointed time for it, the punishment would already have come to them. Indeed it will come down upon them suddenly and catch them unawares"
  29,54,"They ask you to hasten the punishment, but surely, Hell is [already] encompassing those who deny the truth"
  29,55,"On the Day the punishment envelops them from above them and from underneath their feet, they will be told, \"Taste [the punishment] for what you used to do"
  29,56,"My servants who believe, My earth is vast, so worship Me alone"
  29,57,Every soul shall taste death and then to Us you shall return
  29,58,We shall lodge forever those who believe and do good works in the mansions of Paradise beside which rivers flow. How excellent is the reward of those who labour
  29,59,and who are steadfast and put their trust in their Lord
  29,60,"How many creatures cannot fend for themselves! God provides for them and for you. He is the All Hearing, the All Knowing"
  29,61,"If you ask them who it is that has created the heavens and the earth and subjugated the sun and the moon, they will say, \"God.\" How then are they turned away"
  29,62,God gives abundantly to whom He will and sparingly to whom He pleases. God has full knowledge of all things
  29,63,"And if you ask them who it is that sends down water from the sky and revives the earth with it after its death, they will surely answer, \"God.\" Then praise be to God. But most of them do not understand"